<h2 id="test-voltages">Correct Test Voltages</h2>

<Callout type="warning" title="Using the wrong test voltage invalidates the result">
  <p>Too low a voltage won't stress the insulation enough to reveal weak spots. Too high a voltage can damage good insulation. Always use the voltage specified for the equipment rating.</p>
</Callout>

<div class="my-8 rounded-xl border border-gray-200 overflow-hidden">
  <table class="w-full text-sm border-collapse">
    <thead>
      <tr class="bg-[#0D1B2A]">
        <th class="text-left px-5 py-3 text-[#94a3b8] font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-widest">Equipment Rating</th>
        <th class="text-center px-5 py-3 text-white font-semibold">Test Voltage</th>
        <th class="text-center px-5 py-3 text-white font-semibold">Minimum IR (1 min)</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      {[
        ['LT cables and wiring (up to 1000 V)', '500 V DC', '> 1 MΩ'],
        ['Motors and generators (< 1 kV)', '500 V DC', '> 1 MΩ (new), > 0.5 MΩ (service)'],
        ['HT cables and equipment (1–33 kV)', '1000–2500 V DC', '> 100 MΩ'],
        ['Switchgear and busbars', '1000 V DC', '> 100 MΩ'],
        ['Transformers (HV winding)', '2500 V DC', '> 500 MΩ'],
      ].map(([eq, v, r], i) => (
        <tr class={i % 2 === 0 ? 'bg-white' : 'bg-gray-50'}>
          <td class="px-5 py-3 text-[#0D1B2A] font-medium border-b border-gray-100 text-xs">{eq}</td>
          <td class="px-5 py-3 text-center font-mono text-[#E0252E] border-b border-gray-100 text-xs font-bold">{v}</td>
          <td class="px-5 py-3 text-center text-gray-700 border-b border-gray-100 text-xs">{r}</td>
        </tr>
      ))}
    </tbody>
  </table>
</div>

<h2 id="procedure">Test Procedure — Step by Step</h2>

<Callout type="warning" title="Isolate and discharge before testing">
  <p>The equipment must be <strong>completely de-energised</strong>, isolated, locked out, and discharged before connecting the megohmmeter. Capacitive equipment (motors, long cables) will store charge from the test voltage — always discharge via the instrument's built-in discharge function or a discharge resistor after testing.</p>
</Callout>

<div class="my-6 space-y-0">
  {[
    { n:1, t:'Isolate and verify zero voltage', b:'Switch off, lock out, and use a voltage tester to confirm zero volts on all phases and to earth.' },
    { n:2, t:'Disconnect equipment under test', b:'Disconnect cables from switchgear, motors from drives, etc. Test leads of other instruments connected in parallel give false low readings.' },
    { n:3, t:'Connect megohmmeter leads', b:'Connect the Line (L) terminal to the conductor under test. Connect Earth (E) to the equipment frame or earth. Some tests also use a Guard terminal to eliminate surface leakage.' },
    { n:4, t:'Select correct test voltage', b:'Use the table above. Most mains-voltage installations use 500 V DC.' },
    { n:5, t:'Apply voltage for 60 seconds', b:'Press the test button. Note the reading at 15 seconds and at 60 seconds. A rising reading (R60 > R15) indicates good insulation. A falling or stable reading may indicate moisture or contamination.' },
    { n:6, t:'Record and discharge', b:'Note the 1-minute reading. Immediately use the discharge function or hold the test leads connected for 60 seconds after removing voltage to discharge stored charge safely.' },
  ].map((s, i, arr) => (
    <div class="flex gap-4 relative">
      {i < arr.length - 1 && <div class="absolute left-5 top-10 bottom-0 w-0.5 bg-[#E0252E]/20"></div>}
      <div class="shrink-0 w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-[#E0252E] text-white font-bold text-sm flex items-center justify-center z-10 shadow">{s.n}</div>
      <div class="pb-6">
        <p class="font-bold text-[#0D1B2A]">{s.t}</p>
        <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm mt-0.5">{s.b}</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  ))}
</div>

<h2 id="polarisation-index">The Polarisation Index (PI)</h2>

<p>The <strong>Polarisation Index</strong> is the ratio of the 10-minute reading to the 1-minute reading. It is a more reliable indicator of insulation condition than a single reading, because it filters out surface effects.</p>

<div class="my-6 font-mono text-center text-xl font-bold text-[#0D1B2A] p-5 bg-gray-50 rounded-xl border border-gray-200">
  PI = R<sub class="text-sm">10 min</sub> ÷ R<sub class="text-sm">1 min</sub>
</div>

<div class="my-6 grid sm:grid-cols-3 gap-3">
  {[
    { pi:'PI < 1', condition:'Dangerous', color:'bg-red-50 border-red-200 text-red-800' },
    { pi:'PI 1.0 – 2.0', condition:'Questionable / Needs attention', color:'bg-amber-50 border-amber-200 text-amber-800' },
    { pi:'PI > 2.0', condition:'Good insulation condition', color:'bg-emerald-50 border-emerald-200 text-emerald-800' },
  ].map(p => (
    <div class={`p-4 rounded-xl border text-center ${p.color}`}>
      <div class="font-mono font-bold text-lg mb-1">{p.pi}</div>
      <div class="text-xs font-medium">{p.condition}</div>
    </div>
  ))}
</div>

<h2 id="interpreting">Interpreting Your Results</h2>

<p>A single megohm reading in isolation means little — trend analysis over time is far more valuable. Key rules:</p>

<div class="my-6 space-y-2">
  {[
    { ok:true, text:'A reading that is consistent with previous records and above the minimum = insulation is acceptable.' },
    { ok:true, text:'A rising reading during the test (R at 60s > R at 30s) = insulation is absorbing charge normally = healthy polarisation.' },
    { ok:false, text:'A reading 30–50% below previous records = investigate immediately, even if it is above the minimum threshold.' },
    { ok:false, text:'A reading that falls during the test = surface leakage or moisture = dry out and retest before energising.' },
    { ok:false, text:'Zero or very low reading (< 0.5 MΩ on a 500V test) = definite fault. Do not energise.' },
  ].map(rule => (
    <div class={`flex gap-3 items-start p-3.5 rounded-xl ${rule.ok ? 'bg-emerald-50 border border-emerald-200' : 'bg-red-50 border border-red-200'}`}>
      <span class={`shrink-0 w-5 h-5 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-xs font-bold mt-0.5 ${rule.ok ? 'bg-emerald-500 text-white' : 'bg-red-500 text-white'}`}>{rule.ok ? '✓' : '✕'}</span>
      <p class={`text-sm leading-relaxed ${rule.ok ? 'text-emerald-900' : 'text-red-900'}`}>{rule.text}</p>
    </div>
  ))}
</div>

